haas center for public service beyond the speech martin luther king jr day challenge student affairs haas center for public service students faculty alumni community about stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit beyond the speech martin luther king jr day challenge beyond the speech martin luther king jr day challenge haas center for public service life's most persistent and urgent question is what are you doing for others dr martin luther king jr 2011 12 awardees ten service project proposals were submitted to the first beyond the speech martin luther king jr day challenge the proposals involved issues ranging from education and the environment to homelessness and political involvement congratulations to the following service project awardees hope to life submitted by jessica reed 15 burma storytelling event submitted by gillie collins 14 on behalf of stand initiative to promote the vote submitted by michael tubbs 12 on behalf of the naacp stanford chapter it gets better submitted by juan flores 14 on behalf of la familia de stanford the mlk challenge review committee selected these four service projects to share $2000 an increase from the original amount of $1000 the challenge encourages students to plan and implement service projects that extend the celebration and work of dr king beyond one day of service beyond one day of honor and beyond one month of celebration a panel of faculty and staff evaluated the proposals based on the following criteria depth of thought or reflection on dr king's life or message creativity innovation and impact of service project collaboration partnership new audience engagement and new participants visibility and creative marketing management of financial resources the challenge has been made possible by the educational resources division of student affairs the mlk celebration committee and the haas center for public service groups haas center for public service printer friendly version calendar connect with us